1. d4 d5 2. c4 Nc6 $5 3. Nc3 dxc4 $5 { A sharp novelty is played in the Chigorin Defence. It proceeds the sharp play by Black in the Soviet school of chess. } 4. d5 $5 Na5 $5 5. Qa4+ c6 6. b4 b5 $1 7. Qxa5 Qxa5 8. bxa5 b4 9. Nd1 cxd5 10. e4 e6 11. Ne3 ( 11. Be3 $1 { keeps a plus. } ) 11... Nf6 12. exd5 exd5 13. Bb2 $5 Be6 ( 13... c3 $1 14. Bc1 Bc5 { equalises. } ) 15. Bxf6 gxf6 16. Ne2 Rc8 17. Nf4 $5 { White prefers to counter in the centre. } Rc5 18. Rd1 c3 $1 19. a6 Bd6 { Wien has a won position in the other game and takes no risk. } 20. Nfxd5 $5 { White lifts the tension. } ( 20. Nd3 $1 Ra5 21. Nc2 Ra4 { keeps a sharp game going. } ) 22. c2 $1 Rc1 23. Bxd5 Nxd5 24. Rxd5 Rxc2 25. Ke7 g3 26. Ra5 Be2 27. Be5 O-O 28. Rd8 f4 29. Bc3 Rf3 30. Rd6 Kg2 31. f5 Re3+ 32. Kf8 Bf1 33. h6 Bc4 34. Rd4 Bb3 35. Rxa6 Rce2 36. Re4 Rxe4 37. fxe4 Rxe4 38. Rd6 Rc4 39. Rd7 Rc6 40. Kg7 Kf3 41. Bf6 Kg4 42. Bd4 Ba4 43. Re7 Rd6 44. Bg1 { Wien had won the match and 2000 Francs. } 1/2-1/2

