1. e4 e5 2. f4 d5 3. exd5 e4 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. d3 Bb4 6. dxe4 Nxe4 7. Qd4 Bxc3+ ( 7... Qe7 { Even better is (Hemppe-Pitschel, Wien 1859). } ) 8. bxc3 O-O 9. Nf3 Re8 10. Be2 Bg4 11. O-O Nxc3 $2 12. Qxc3 Rxe2 { Black has an  awful position. } 13. Bb2 Qf8 $6 ( 13... f6 { A lesser evil is } 14. Nd4 Re8 ) 15. Nd4 Re4 16. Qd3 Qe7 17. Ne6 $5 ( 17. Ba3 $1 Qe8 18. Ne6 $1 { ends the game. } ) 18... Re2 19. Nd4 $2 ( 19. Ba3 $1 { Right is } Qd7 20. f5 $1 fxe6 21. fxe6 Qe8 22. Rf8+ ) 22... Re3 $1 23. Qd2 Na6 24. f5 f6 25. h3 Bh5 26. Ne6 Re4 27. Rae1 Rxe1 28. Rxe1 Re8 29. Re3 Bf7 30. Ba3 Qd7 31. Rd3 c5 32. dxc6 $2 { White expects to start a fatal combination. } Qxc6 33. Nxg7 $5 Kxg7 34. Rg3+ Bg6 $2 { Walbrodt misses the great escape. } ( 34... Kh8 $1 { Correct is } 35. Qh6 Qb6+ 36. Kh2 Rg8 37. Be7 Rxg3 { (Tarrasch) } 38. Qf8+ $1 Rg8 39. Qxf7 Rxg2+ $1 40. Kxg2 Qc6+ { and Black can deliver perpetual check. } ) 41. fxg6 hxg6 42. Bc1 g5 $6 43. Bb2 Kg6 44. Rf3 Re6 45. Qd3+ Kg7 46. Rg3 Qc5+ 47. Bd4 Qa5 48. h4 Nc5 $2 49. Rxg5+ $1 Kf7 50. Qh7+ Ke8 51. Rg8# { Tarrasch won the master tournament with a score of 13 1/2 out of 17 and gained 800 Mark. } 1-0

