1. e4 { Notes by J. Lowenthal } e5 2. f4 c5 3. Nf3 d6 4. Bc4 Qf6 { It is rarely, if ever, advisable to play the queen thus early in the game.  Her position is not a good one either for attack or defence, and she is often subjected to a most embarrasing attack here. } 5. Nc3 Be6 { Taking the pawn with queen, would clearly have been bad. } 6. Bb5+ Nc6 7. f5 Bd7 8. O-O Qd8 9. d3 Be7 10. g4 h6 11. Be3 Nd4 12. Bxd7+ Qxd7 13. Nd5 Nf6 14. Nxf6+ Bxf6 15. c3 Nc6 16. c4 g5 17. Nd2 b6 18. Nb1 Ne7 19. Nc3 a6 20. Rb1 Qc6 21. b4 Kd7 22. Nd5 Nxd5 { Compulsory, as by retreating the bishop to g7, Whit would win a piece by f6. } 23. cxd5 Qc7 24. bxc5 bxc5 25. Qa4+ Ke7 26. Rb3 Rhb8 27. Rfb1 Rxb3 28. Qxb3 Kf8 29. Qb7 Qxb7 30. Rxb7 Be7 31. Kf1 1/2-1/2

