1. e4 { August 31 Morphy and Edge took the channel steamship to France ... Saturday saw the arrival of Harrwitz. Morphy went against his usual custom of waiting to be challenged and asked Harrwitz if he would be interested  in a match. Harrwitz acted reluctant to play a match but offered to play a casual game with Morphy. Harrwitz played the King's Gambit and won the game. He immediately accepted Morphy's challenge of a match. The match started on September 5th - SBC Bio-8 } e5 2. f4 exf4 3. Nf3 g5 4. h4 g4 5. Ne5 Nf6 6. Bc4 d5 7. exd5 Bd6 8. d4 Nh5 9. Bb5+ c6 10. dxc6 O-O 11. cxb7 Bxb7 12. Qxg4+ Ng7 13. Bxf4 Qb6 14. Nc3 Bxe5 15. Bxe5 f6 16. Bg3 Na6 17. O-O Rad8 18. Rad1 Kh8 19. Bxa6 Bxa6 20. Rfe1 Bc8 21. Qf3 Bb7 22. Qd3 Rd7 23. Qb5 Qd8 24. d5 Nf5 25. Bf2 Rg8 26. Qd3 Rdg7 27. Qxf5 Rxg2+ 28. Kf1 Ba6+ 29. Ne2 Qd6 30. Rd3 Bxd3 31. cxd3 Rh2 32. Nf4 Rh1+ 33. Ke2 Rh2 34. Ne6 Rg6 35. Rc1 Qb8 36. b3 Rgg2 37. Qxf6+ Kg8 38. Ke3 Rh3+ 39. Ke2 Rxf2+ 40. Qxf2 Rh2 41. Rg1+ Kh8 42. Rg2 Qe5+ 43. Kf3 Qxd5+ 44. Kg3 Rxg2+ 45. Qxg2 Qxe6 46. Qa8+ Kg7 47. Qxa7+ 1-0

